        <updateDate>2016-04-06T13:56:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>ABLE Age Adjustment Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to qualified ABLE programs, to increase the &nbsp;threshold for eligibility for such programs from age 26 to age 46. (Tax-favored ABLE [Achieving a Better Life Experience] accounts are designed to enable individuals with disabilities to save for and pay for disability-related expenses.)</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
